text: MUF or muf may refer to: * MUF (programming language), "Multi-User Forth" * Main Uralian Fault, in the Ural Mountains of Russia * Maximum usable frequency, for radio transmissions * Moderata Ungdomsförbundet, or Moderate Youth League, Sweden * Manchester United Football Ground railway station, UK, station code * IATA code for Muting Airport, Indonesia * muf, London collaborative of artists and architects * Muslim United Front, Kashmiri political coalition ==See also== * Muff (disambiguation)
title: Muf (disambiguation)
